<section id="command-penreverse">
<title>PENREVERSE</title>
<indexterm><primary>PENREVERSE</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>PX</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PENREVERSE</command>
<command>PX</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Sets the pen's position to "down" and the pen's mode to "reverse".
In reverse mode, the pen draws in a color that is the bitwise negation of whatever pixel is under the pen.
Use <link linkend="command-penpaint">PENPAINT</link> to restore the pen to normal use.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETPENCOLOR [255 0 0]
PENPAINT
FORWARD 100
PENREVERSE
BACK 100</userinput></programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-penerase">PENERASE</link></member>
<member><link linkend="command-penpaint">PENPAINT</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
